Privacy Policy – Texas Daily

Last updated: December 2025

Texas Daily respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the Texas Daily mobile application.

⸻

Information We Collect

Texas Daily does not collect, store, or share personal information such as names, email addresses, phone numbers, or precise location data.

The app may process the following locally on your device:
	•	App preferences (such as theme selection)
	•	Notification reminder time
	•	In-app purchase status (to remove ads)

This data is stored only on your device using Apple’s standard system storage and is not transmitted to our servers.

⸻

Advertising

Texas Daily displays advertisements using Google AdMob.

Ad providers may collect limited, non-personal information such as:
	•	Device identifiers
	•	Approximate location
	•	Usage data related to ads

This data is handled according to Google’s Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

You may remove ads at any time through a one-time in-app purchase.

⸻

In-App Purchases

Texas Daily offers a one-time in-app purchase to remove advertisements. Purchases are processed securely by Apple via StoreKit. Texas Daily does not receive or store payment information.

⸻

Notifications

If enabled, Texas Daily uses local notifications to deliver a daily Texas fact at a time you choose. Notification scheduling is handled entirely on your device.

⸻

Data Sharing

Texas Daily does not sell, rent, or share personal data with third parties.

⸻

Security

Texas Daily relies on Apple’s built-in security features and system APIs to protect app data. No custom encryption methods are implemented.

⸻

Children’s Privacy

Texas Daily does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

⸻

Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated occasionally. Any changes will be reflected on this page.

⸻

Contact

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:

Texas Daily Support
